### Variables
@host = http://localhost:8080
@token = PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

### 2. Login (copy the returned `token` into the @token variable above)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

### 3. (M4 Requirement) Create a new note (POST)
POST {{host}}/api/notes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Note Title",
  "content": "This is the content for my test note.",
  "tags": "test, java",
  "pinned": false,
  "inTrash": false,
  "color": "#33aaff"
}

### 4. Get all active notes (GET)
GET {{host}}/api/notes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 5. Get all trashed notes (GET)
GET {{host}}/api/notes/trash
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 6. Get a single note (GET by ID)
# Note: You must run the POST request first to get an ID.
GET {{host}}/api/notes/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 7. Update a note (PUT)
PUT {{host}}/api/notes/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "UPDATED Note Title",
  "content": "The content has been updated.",
  "tags": "test, updated",
  "pinned": true,
  "inTrash": false,
  "color": "#55cc55"
}

### 8. Move a note to trash
PUT {{host}}/api/notes/trash/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Restore a note from trash
PUT {{host}}/api/notes/restore/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Permanently delete a note
DELETE {{host}}/api/notes/permanent/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Download a note as PDF
GET {{host}}/api/notes/1/download/pdf
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/pdf
